Program: Last Word
Title: Otto von Habsburg, Cy Twombly, Anna Massey, Robin Nash and Robert Widmer
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b012942j
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 10 Jul 2011
John Wilson on The great American abstract expressionist painter Cy Twombly. Otto von Habsburg, the last heir to Austro-Hungarian empire who was exiled as a child and later became a campaigning MEP. Anna Massey, star of stage, screen - and Radio 4's This Sceptred Isle. Robert Widmer - inventor of the supersonic bomber. And Robin Nash, who directed some of BBC television's biggest hits - including Top of the Pops - is remembered by Tony Blackburn. Show less